body:
Midoriya Izuku x Reader

If anyone had met Izuku’s mom, they would know what a sweet and accepting woman she is. Dating Izuku gave you a rare insight on the woman, and seeing as the holidays are coming up, you decided to surprise Izuku’s mom with some homemade gingerbread cookies.

You recruited Izuku to assist you in your baking adventure, and to be honest, baking with Izuku was the best. He always followed the directions to a T, and if he wasnt helping or watching you mix the batter, his arms were circled around your waist with his head resting in your shoulder.

“Izuku, do you know your mom’s favorite color? I want the gingerbread men to all have matching little icing bow-ties.” Izuku stayed silent for a bit, mulling it over in his head while he hummed and rocked you back and forth in his arms. Finally, he answered, “I don’t know her favorite color, but she does have a pinky colored sweater that she seems to really like. She wears it almost all the time.”

You hummed, subconsciously leaning back into Izuku’s chest before getting into action and addint a drop or two of red food coloring to the icing to turn it a soft pink. “I hope your mom likes these, she’s such a sweet woman.” You paused, giggled, then continued with, “I bet you get your sweet personality from your mom.”

You felt his body go tense before a breathy laugh escapes his lungs. “I will admit, having mom raise me really helped out. But, you’re also sweet and don’t forget that.” Izuku planted a sweet kiss to your left cheek, then the right, peppering kisses everywhere he could reach before turning your body to him slightly and planting a soft, passionate kiss to your lips. “Come on, Izu, let’s finish these cookies. After they’re done, we can watch whatever movie you want.”

The Midoriya’s may not be the most “average” family, but they are the sweetest and you’re more than happy to stay if they let you.
